@Libaishun yes, the mish implementation uses up a lot of GPU ram when training. Perhaps there are more memory friendly implementations. Currently I simply have:

https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/18702c96084557d020cccf11fc77d8db2e44c073/utils/layers.py#L121-L123

@anhnktp I have not trained yolov4.cfg yet, I simply ported it over from alexeyab/darknet. But yes you are correct, it is not compatible with yolov3-spp-ultralytics.pt, as these pretrained weights are based on yolov3-spp.cfg. And yes training from scratch will always produce lower initial mAPs, don't worry about that. What is important is the final mAP.
